task.summary: Created test project for parsing directions from XML to a domain mode in Java.

Built a string repository for constant optional request parameter options. Created http request factory for generating URL's to send off to Google direction services. Started work on attempting to setup the read function for the output stream that the unparsed XML file will be read from. I'm going to need to brush up on JAXB or find other means to parse the XML. XPath can do it I believe, but I'll have to double check.

Added my current tasks that I have partially completed, as well as tasks that have yet to be completed that I've discovered through today's work thus far. Added a TODO in RequestFactory for setting up JAXB or XPATH
Made more edits to the request factory to accommodate for multiple optional way-points. needs to be finished.

Switched back and forth between a few different methods for getting the XML document from the response sent back by Google direction services. Finally decided (I think) to go with JAXB for creating the XML document, and XPath to navigate the XML document to extract information. So far still working on constructing the proper URL used to request for directions from Google direction services.
Finished building document received from http response. Unsure of whether or not it functions properly, will test first thing tomorrow.
Updated tasks to reflect today's added tasks.
Finalized url creation in requestFactory. Created test activity for sending test request.
Got the app to launch in my emulator. It currently crashes due to the URL being constructed incorrectly. Need to fix the way the parameters are extracted and then compiled into a single url.

There's something 'wonky' with the ordering of my url parameter map's key set. I put into the map the parameter names according to the order I desire, and it iterates through them in a different and sort of obscure order. Need to research a little deeper on how the collection/iterator handle said iteration.

For some reason, 'it' doesn't like line 55 in requestFactory. It is supposed to execute a new http request and in response, google is supposed to send back xml data. The line takes both POST and GET requests, both of which I have tried, neither yield a proper result. Will work out tomorrow. Adding to tasks list.
Been working on getting a successful connection to google service from within an Android app. Setup a URLConnection as opposed to an HTTP service. Testing later today.

Discovered that I need to execute my network connections and such on another thread other than the main thread. AsyncTask's accomplish this via a build in 'service'. Started working with and and making progress towards receiving content from the response.
